#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_multimesh.rst:17
msgid "Description"
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_multimesh.rst:19
msgid ""
"MultiMesh provides low-level mesh instancing. Drawing thousands of "
":ref:`MeshInstance <class_MeshInstance>` nodes can be slow, since each "
"object is submitted to the GPU then drawn individually."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_multimesh.rst:21
msgid ""
"MultiMesh is much faster as it can draw thousands of instances with a "
"single draw call, resulting in less API overhead."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_multimesh.rst:23
msgid ""
"As a drawback, if the instances are too far away of each other, "
"performance may be reduced as every single instance will always rendered "
"(they are spatially indexed as one, for the whole object)."
msgstr ""

#: /home/bee/code/godot/godot-docs-l10n/docs/classes/class_multimesh.rst:25
msgid ""
"Since instances may have any behavior, the AABB used for visibility must "
"be provided by the user."
msgstr ""

